%% Diagram: Refresh-token rotation with reuse detection (RFC 9700)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant AuthZ as Authorization Server
    participant DB as Token family store
    participant Attacker

    Note over Client,DB: Normal rotation
    Client->>AuthZ: POST /token (refresh_token=R1)
    AuthZ->>DB: Lookup family for R1
    DB-->>AuthZ: family=F, R1=active
    AuthZ->>DB: Mark R1 used, issue R2 in F
    AuthZ-->>Client: access=A2, refresh=R2

    Note over Client,DB: Attacker also captures R1 (XSS, log leak, ...)
    Client->>AuthZ: POST /token (refresh_token=R2)
    AuthZ->>DB: R2 active, rotate to R3
    AuthZ-->>Client: access=A3, refresh=R3

    Note over Client,Attacker: Reuse detected — entire family revoked
    Attacker->>AuthZ: POST /token (refresh_token=R1) [reused]
    AuthZ->>DB: R1 already used → compromise of family F
    AuthZ->>DB: Revoke F (R1, R2, R3, all access tokens)
    AuthZ-->>Attacker: 401 invalid_grant
    Note over Client: Next request 401 → re-authenticate
